{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Child bin-packing for container criteria (pack small children, preserve single-child fallback)\n\n## Why\nAfter merge, the container still makes one call per child. Many children are small — multiple WHOLE children fit\nin one call. Packing them reduces calls further, and because G3/G4 are CROSS-CHILD criteria, seeing children\ntogether can IMPROVE consistency detection. Large (parent+child) pairings must keep the single-child path\n(ca03 window-fit guarantee).\n\n## What\n- Bin-pack whole children into one call up to a token budget = model-window x P8_HEADROOM - output reserve\n  (reuse the existing `pair_tokens`/`budget` + P8 machinery). Each child stays WHOLE (never chunked — ca03).\n- PRESERVE the single-child path when parent+child strains the window; a child that alone exceeds budget stays\n  the existing \"too-big -> reduce the ticket\" failure finding.\n- Structured per-child sections in the prompt + REQUIRED per-child output so per-child attention isn't lost.\n- Gate behind an OFFLINE EVAL confirming no per-child attention/accuracy loss vs one-child-per-call.\n\n## Scope\n- In: the bin-packer; multi-child container prompt + required per-child output; single-child fallback; the eval.\n- Out: merge (S4, dependency); the caching/parallel substrate (S1/S3).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Small children are packed into one call up to the window budget; each child whole (never chunked).\n- [ ] A child whose (parent+child) strains the window keeps its own call; a single child exceeding budget yields\n      the too-big failure finding.\n- [ ] The prompt requires per-child output; an offline eval shows no per-child attention/accuracy loss vs one-per-call.\n- [ ] Container call count drops below N for epics with small children; `make lint` + tests pass.\n\n## Remediation (opus review — MAJOR 5, MINOR 10, BLOCKER 3)\n- Bin budget reuses `int(largest_window_tokens * P8_HEADROOM) - P8_OUTPUT_RESERVE_TOKENS` (pass1.py:57-59), summed\n  over `parent + ALL packed children`; the single-child fallback (`pair_tokens > budget`) still fires for a lone\n  oversized child -> the existing too-big failure finding, unchanged.\n- Update the sizing.py container-cost projection for <N calls after packing.\n- Fidelity gate = the S6 semantic eval harness (DEPENDS ON S6).\n- [ ] Bin budget = parent + all packed children <= P8 window budget; a lone child exceeding it yields the existing\n      too-big failure finding; each child whole (never chunked).\n- [ ] sizing.py projection reflects the reduced (<N) call count after packing.\n- [ ] The S6 fidelity harness shows packed-call findings within tolerance of one-child-per-call.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782544918157113001,"uuid":"8960f893-b17c-44f4-aa1c-91e6f6f8a777"}